  🔠 call_00_ZrjsKk27VkIC1TTJK44f1671 | Return {'query': {'original': 'Kafka vs Redis Streams comparison notification system throughput ordering guarantees', 'show_strict_warning': False, 'is_navigational': False, 'is_news_breaking': False, 'spellcheck_off': False, 'country': 'us', 'bad_results': False, 'should_fallback': False, 'postal_code': '', 'city': '', 'header_country': '', 'more_results_available': True, 'state': ''}, 'results': [{'title': 'Redis Streams vs Kafka: A Detailed Comparison', 'url': 'https://oneuptime.com/blog/post/2026-03-31-redis-streams-vs-kafka-detailed-comparison/view', 'snippet': 'You already operate Redis and want to avoid introducing Kafka. Message volume fits in memory with a bounded retention window. Simple consumer group semantics without cross-partition ordering concerns. Development simplicity and fast iteration matter more than extreme scale. You need infinite message retention on disk. Throughput exceeds a million messages per second.', 'source': 'brave'}, {'title': 'Redis OSS vs Kafka - Difference Between Pub/Sub Messaging Systems - AWS', 'url': 'https://aws.amazon.com/compare/the-difference-between-kafka-and-redis/', 'snippet': 'However, Kafka&#x27;s performance may decrease if consumers are not retrieving the message fast enough, as unread messages on the cache are eventually removed. In this case, consumers must read from the disk, which is slower. Meanwhile, Redis OSS must wait for acknowledgment for each consumer, which significantly decreases its throughput with more connected nodes.', 'source': 'brave'}, {'title': 'Redis streams vs. Kafka | Matt Westcott', 'url': 'https://mattwestcott.org/blog/redis-streams-vs-kafka', 'snippet': 'It therefore <strong>loses the ordering guarantee that is central to stream processing</strong>, which is rather unfortunate. So how can we build a stream processing engine on top of Redis if it only offers effectively a single partition of a topic with job-queue ...', 'source': 'brave'}, {'title': 'Redis vs Kafka: A comprehensive comparison for developers | DoubleCloud', 'url': 'https://double.cloud/blog/posts/2024/02/redis-vs-kafka/', 'snippet': 'In summary, <strong>Apache Kafka is optimized for scaling to extremely high throughputs, volumes and durable retention of large event streams</strong> whereas Redis emphasizes blazing fast in-memory speed for smaller transient data needing low millisecond response ...', 'source': 'brave'}, {'title': 'Redis Pub/Sub vs Kafka Topics: When to Use Which', 'url': 'https://oneuptime.com/blog/post/2026-03-31-redis-pubsub-vs-kafka-topics-when-to-use-which/view', 'snippet': 'from confluent_kafka import Producer, ... {msg.value().decode()}&quot;) consumer.commit() <strong>Redis Streams fills the gap between Pub/Sub and Kafka by adding persistence and consumer groups</strong>:...', 'source': 'brave'}, {'title': 'Real-Time Event Streaming: Kafka vs Redis Streams vs NATS in 2026 - DEV Community', 'url': 'https://dev.to/young_gao/real-time-event-streaming-kafka-vs-redis-streams-vs-nats-in-2026-34o1', 'snippet': 'Each has different strengths, and ... real code, benchmarks, and decision criteria. <strong>Kafka excels when you need guaranteed delivery, massive throughput, and long-term retention</strong>....', 'source': 'brave'}, {'title': 'Redis Streams vs Kafka Streams: A Detailed Comparison', 'url': 'https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/redis-streams-vs-kafka-detailed-comparison-abinash-mishra', 'snippet': '<strong>Each entry in a Redis Stream has a unique ID based on a timestamp, ensuring data is ordered even when added simultaneously</strong>. Kafka Streams: Kafka Streams is a client library for building applications and microservices, where the input and output ...', 'source': 'brave'}, {'title': 'Redis vs Kafka for Message Queuing', 'url': 'https://oneuptime.com/blog/post/2026-03-31-redis-vs-kafka-for-message-queuing/view', 'snippet': '<strong>Redis is a fast in-memory store with Streams and Pub/Sub added on top.</strong> Kafka is a distributed commit log built from the ground up for durable, high-throughput event streaming. Picking the wrong one is a common architectural mistake.', 'source': 'brave'}, {'title': 'Redis vs Kafka | What are the differences? | StackShare', 'url': 'https://stackshare.io/stackups/kafka-vs-redis', 'snippet': 'In Redis, data processing capabilities are limited, and it mainly focuses on data storage and retrieval operations. Consistency and Ordering: <strong>Kafka guarantees the ordering of messages within each partition of a topic, providing strong consistency</strong>.', 'source': 'brave'}, {'title': 'Redis™ Streams vs Apache Kafka® - Instaclustr', 'url': 'https://www.instaclustr.com/blog/redis-streams-vs-apache-kafka/', 'snippet': '<strong>Kafka uses topic partitions for high concurrency and throughput</strong>, supporting multiple consumers sharing the message processing load and multi-threading/multiple nodes on the server-side as well.', 'source': 'brave'}], 'total': 10, 'page': 1, 'error': None}
